name: Recoleta Cementery
description: The Recoleta Cemetery is a famous cemetery in the city of Buenos Aires, Argentina. It is located in the Recoleta neighborhood and contains the tombs of well-known people. It was inaugurated on November 17, 1822, during the government of Brigadier General Martín Rodríguez, while Bernardino Rivadavia was Minister of Government. It thus became the first public cemetery in the city.

name: Obelisco
description: The Obelisk of Buenos Aires is a historical monument considered an icon of the Autonomous City of Buenos Aires, the capital of Argentina. It was built in 1936 on the occasion of the fourth centenary of the so-called first foundation of Buenos Aires by Pedro de Mendoza. It is located in the Plaza de la República, at the intersection of Corrientes and 9 de Julio avenues, in the San Nicolás neighborhood in Buenos Aires.

name: Cristo Redentor
description: Christ the Redeemer or Cristo del Corcovado is an art deco statue of Jesus of Nazareth, with open arms, showing the city of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. The statue has a height of thirty meters on an eight meter pedestal. This monument was inaugurated on October 12, 1931 after approximately 5 years of construction.

name: Pan de Azúcar
description: The Sugar Loaf is a rock located in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, at the mouth of Guanabara Bay on a peninsula jutting out into the Atlantic Ocean.

name: Gardens by the Bay
description: Gardens by the Bay is a 101-hectare park in Singapore built on reclaimed land in the Central Singapore region, adjacent to the marine reserve. It is formed by three landscaped margins: Central, East and South, the latter being the largest with 54 ha. The park is part of the Government's policies to make Singapore a 'city within a garden' with the initial objective of 'improving the quality of life together with the flora and fauna' of the city. In January 2006, an international competition began to deliver projects.

name: Singapore Zoo
description: Singapore Zoo is a 28-hectare zoological garden on the upper banks of the Seletar Reservoir within Singapore's heavily forested central basin. The zoo was built at a cost of $9 million paid by the Singapore government and opened on June 27, 1973.

name: Tower of London
description: The Tower of London, officially Her Majesty's Royal Palace and Fortress, is a historic castle situated on the north bank of the River Thames in central London, England. It is located within the London Borough of Tower Hamlets, separated from the northern city limits by an open space known as Tower Hill. It was founded towards the end of 1066 as part of the Norman conquest of England.

name: London Eye
description: The London Eye is a large Ferris wheel located on the South Bank of the River Thames in London, United Kingdom. It is the tallest Ferris wheel in Europe and the most popular tourist attraction in the UK with over 3.75 million visitors a year. It is 135m high and the circle of the Ferris wheel has a diameter of 120m.

name: Sensō-ji
description: Sensō-ji is a Buddhist temple located in Asakusa, Tokyo, Japan. It is the oldest temple in Tokyo and one of the most important. It is associated with the Tendai Buddhist sect, from which it became independent after World War II. Next to the temple is the Asakusa Shinto Shrine.

name: Shinjuku Gyoen National Garden
description: Shinjuku Gyoen National Garden is a 58.3-hectare botanical garden in Shinjuku, Tokyo Prefecture, Japan. It is administered by the National Ministry of the Environment. Presents papers for the International Agenda Registration.

name: Saint Basil's Cathedral
description: The Temple of the Intercession of the Blessed Virgin over the moat, better known as the Temple of Saint Basil, is an Orthodox temple located on Red Square in the city of Moscow, Russia. It is world famous for its bulbous domes.

name: Moscow Kremlin
description: The Moscow Kremlin is a complex of civil and religious buildings located in the center of Moscow, facing the Moskva River in the south, the Red Square in the east and the Alexander Garden in the west. It is the best known of the Russian Kremlins and includes four palaces and four cathedrals, grouped within an enclosure bounded by the Kremlin Wall, which includes the Kremlin towers.
